<subSubSection id="9707CC4688E07B8901CE4F2B62112CE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" type="type species">
<paragraph id="53520923FD7A61E542F80CE44748AA56" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6766C3CD2BA7AD16978C906BFBCB2F9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">
<taxonomicName id="C5382EAF4EDFDA7ACE9F2FCFA6E1D080" authority="Falniowski, 2021" authorityName="Hofman &amp; Grego" authorityYear="2021" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Achaiohydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Achaiohydrobia moreana" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="moreana">
<emphasis id="C0E1E142616849A305EC2B7C75A7CD72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Achaiohydrobia moreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by monophyly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="287F17C28C9125DB8C6A04F13DFC4DD4" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="24F8ED349C0B14777F127E0B19439A8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00A2F87232FABCC792A17241FF7BE21B" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Shell broad, ovate-conic with a few flat whorls, rapidly growing and separated by a moderately deep suture; female reproductive organs with prominent, massive swelling of the spiral of the oviduct; oval bursa copulatrix with the duct longer than the bursa, receptaculum seminis prominent but smaller than the bursa, with the duct slightly distinguishable; penis tapering, widened at the base, without any outgrowths (nonglandular lobes) and without the distal papilla.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70D3536F0D62817955C9D8139A23A9F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8056D179661587964E671F1F28A12649" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Derivatio nominis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2070BF203993819C6CE5B3962B6BC2B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">The genus name refers to Achaia, one of the ancient names of Greece and the Greek people.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E403D3742FF2BD940EDB680E7AAFB275" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="402BE06FD65ECF3C0F67083B194F3667" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="05DFE3C783309464FFEA5E55AB27C101" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">
The tapering penis with its broad base distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="CCD1ED48A45F45DB18E1B07B6A0D263D" authority="Falniowski, 2021" authorityName="Falniowski" authorityYear="2021" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Achaiohydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Achaiohydrobia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E8695490F9971F088826A43693EC8124" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Achaiohydrobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="1C5612175A892B982E630A0A85387CC6" authorityName="W. Hartmann" authorityYear="1821" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Hydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hydrobia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5DA1FFE7E9417FEB2D97DCEEB848BF69" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Hydrobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="240B0850A7EBB864C8A3ED5D9A28344C" authorityName="Paladilhe" authorityYear="1874" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Peringia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peringia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="47EA6F55DEF8E098C98D9FFADDB831CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Peringia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The lack of any non-glandular outgrowths (lobes) distinguishes it from 
<taxonomicName id="9F3E2815203D888B14E8CAA58104AF13" authorityName="W. Hartmann" authorityYear="1821" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Hydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hydrobia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E6A2E9A6630657C4B6AD988E438FE883" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Hydrobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="FE9C8253685D898E71598860D0665C86" authorityName="Paladilhe" authorityYear="1874" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Peringia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peringia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F6B0CF1919F145B3C7C5E23D63797A93" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Peringia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="1C0A4D166F5E223A38532D2ED24FBBD9" authorityName="Radoman" authorityYear="1977" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Ventrosia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ventrosia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E1E0C9A5CCBFDBC3F1184D3E5657730F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Ventrosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The lack of the distal papilla on the penis distinguishes it from 
<taxonomicName id="6EF514800EB81E3E9136A2692457CA35" authorityName="Wilke" authorityYear="2003" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Salenthydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salenthydrobia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F47667E21F3B6EC95AB619ABEC20906F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Salenthydrobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The massive swelling of the long spiral renal oviduct differentiates 
<taxonomicName id="F55ED6553E32EABAB94A8421852C03C6" authority="Falniowski, 2021" authorityName="Falniowski" authorityYear="2021" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Achaiohydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Achaiohydrobia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="627A5498D836A7FEF7CBAEB9E424A7D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Achaiohydrobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other genera besides 
<taxonomicName id="D62C590AF295EE8ACB9792709FA2F05A" authorityName="W. Hartmann" authorityYear="1821" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Hydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hydrobia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EE87604381EE7D7E0B0DC9FF7929E703" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Hydrobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The molecular divergence between 
<taxonomicName id="E98EB2BAC0523E4C7AF4EF508A0DBD5C" authority="Falniowski, 2021" authorityName="Falniowski" authorityYear="2021" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Achaiohydrobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Achaiohydrobia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="64260D222320E89724A49253D360D147" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Achaiohydrobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other genera (
<emphasis id="CFF64195E367955D223FE0DBE82BAC7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">p</emphasis>
= 0.109-0.167 for mitochondrial COI) is typical of the genus-level in 
<taxonomicName id="D4630F8B759099527589E3692E91A85A" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Hydrobiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
